    <snippet id="predefined_error_messages">
        <chapter title="Predefined Error Messages" id="predefined-error-messages">
            <note title="Errors detailing">
                Detailed error log is stored in a separate file for each failed request (with <code>Logged Error Message</code> msg).
                In response,
                we return more user-friendly message (as listed in <code>Response Error Message</code> column below).
            </note>
            <tip>
                All values in curly braces <code>{ }</code> will be substituted with actual data.
                Note, that <code>{id}</code> will be substituted with request id.
            </tip>
            <table style="both">
                <tr>
                    <td sorted="asc">Error Name</td>
                    <td>Logged Error Message</td>
                    <td>Response Error Message</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>ERR_ENV_VAR_NOT_SET</td>
                    <td>Environment variable {var} is not set</td>
                    <td>Internal error ({id}). Ask for support</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>ERR_FILE_NOT_EXISTS</td>
                    <td>File '{file_path}' does not exist</td>
                    <td>We cannot find your file ({id}). Try again</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>ERR_FILE_IS_NOT_READABLE</td>
                    <td>File is not readable: {file_path}</td>
                    <td>Internal error ({id}). Ask for support</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>ERR_GENERAL</td>
                    <td>General error: {err}</td>
                    <td>General error ({id}). Ask for support</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>ERR_GET_FILE_CLOUD</td>
                    <td>Download error for {src_path}: local file {local_path} not exists</td>
                    <td>Cannot download your file from the cloud storage ({id}). Try again</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>ERR_INFERENCE</td>
                    <td>Inference error: {inference_traceback}</td>
                    <td>Something went wrong during inference process ({id}). Try again</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>ERR_INFERENCE_INVALID_CONVERTED_FILE</td>
                    <td>Inference error: output file {out} does not exists or empty</td>
                    <td>Something went wrong during inference process ({id}). Try again</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>ERR_INVALID_AUDIO_FILE</td>
                    <td>Invalid audio file {file_path}\n{ffmpeg_err}</td>
                    <td>Your file is not suitable for conversion ({id}). Ask for support</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>ERR_INVALID_CONTEXT</td>
                    <td>Invalid context {context}</td>
                    <td>Internal error ({id}). Ask for support</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>ERR_INVALID_PROCESSING_MODE</td>
                    <td>Invalid processing mode {mode}</td>
                    <td>Internal error ({id}). Ask for support</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>ERR_INVALID_FILE_FOR_PROCESSING</td>
                    <td>File is invalid for further processing</td>
                    <td>Your file is not suitable for conversion ({id}). Ask for support</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>ERR_INVALID_FILE_PITCH</td>
                    <td>File has highest pitch {file_f0max} while selected model is capable only up to {model_f0max}</td>
                    <td>Sorry, but this voice cannot hit such high notes ({id}). Select other voice</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>ERR_INVALID_MODEL_AGE</td>
                    <td>Wrong age value for a model instance: {age}</td>
                    <td>Internal error ({id}). Ask for support</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>ERR_INVALID_MODEL_GENDER</td>
                    <td>Wrong gender value for a model instance: {gender}</td>
                    <td>Internal error ({id}). Ask for support</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>ERR_INVALID_MODEL_METADATA_FILE</td>
                    <td>Invalid json content in models metadata file: {file_path}</td>
                    <td>Internal error ({id}). Ask for support</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>ERR_INVALID_PAYLOAD</td>
                    <td>Invalid payload: {err}</td>
                    <td>Something wrong with your request ({id}). Ask for support</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>ERR_LONG_DURATION</td>
                    <td>Audio file too long: {duration}s</td>
                    <td>Your audio is too long, max allowed duration is {max_duration} min ({id}).</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>ERR_LOW_LOUDNESS_LEVEL</td>
                    <td>Audio file too quiet, RMS is {rms}dB and LUSFS is {lufs}dB</td>
                    <td>Your audio is too quiet, try to increase loudness level above {min_rms}dB ({id}).</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>ERR_MODEL_METADATA_API_FETCH</td>
                    <td>Model metadata api request to {url} failed with code {code} and message {message}</td>
                    <td>Internal error ({id}). Ask for support</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>ERR_MODEL_NOT_FOUND</td>
                    <td>Model file not found: {model}</td>
                    <td>We cannot find a voice you selected for processing ({id}). Ask for support</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>ERR_NO_AUDIO_STREAM</td>
                    <td>File does not contain audio stream</td>
                    <td>Your audio file does not seem to contain actual audio ({id}). Check your file</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>ERR_NO_RMS_VALUE</td>
                    <td>Failed to calculate RMS level for file {file_path}\n{stdout_err}</td>
                    <td>Something went wrong during RMS level detection ({id}). Ask for support</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>ERR_NO_LUFS_VALUE</td>
                    <td>Failed to calculate LUFS level for file {file_path}\n{stdout_err}</td>
                    <td>Something went wrong during LUFS level detection ({id}). Ask for support</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>ERR_PAYLOAD_KEY_NOT_EXISTS</td>
                    <td>Key {key} does not exist in payload</td>
                    <td>Something wrong with your request ({id}). Ask for support</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>ERR_PUT_FILE_CLOUD</td>
                    <td>Upload error for {dst_path}: local file {src_path} not exists</td>
                    <td>Cannot upload your file to the cloud storage ({id}). Try again</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>ERR_SHORT_DURATION</td>
                    <td>Audio file too short: {duration}s</td>
                    <td>Your audio is too short, it should have a duration at least {min_duration}s ({id}).</td>
                </tr>

            </table>
        </chapter>
    </snippet>

    <snippet id="audio_file_requirements">
        <note title="Audio File Requirements">
            <list type="bullet">
                <li>The following file types are supported: aif, aiff, wav, mp3, ogg, flac, ac3, m4a</li>
                <li>Audio RMS volume should be greater than -40dB</li>
                <li>Min length for audio is 1 second</li>
                <li>Max length is 30 minutes</li>
            </list>
        </note>
    </snippet>

    <snippet id="video_files_note">
        <note title="Video files">
            Supported formats: mp4, avi, mov, flv, wmv, mkv. Other formats might work as well because under the hood
            Voicerary is using <code>ffmpeg</code> to get an audio stream from video file.
        </note>
    </snippet>

    <snippet id="common_request_params">
        <chapter title="Common Request Parameters" id="common_request_parameters"
                 collapsible="true" default-state="expanded">
            <table style="both">
                <tr>
                    <td>Parameter</td>
                    <td>Required/Optional</td>
                    <td>Data Type</td>
                    <td>Description</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>input.mode</td>
                    <td>required</td>
                    <td>string</td>
                    <td>
                        <p>Processing mode:</p>
                        <list>
                            <li><control>single</control>: convert single file with a single model</li>
                            <li><control>preview</control>: convert single file with one or more models.
                                For input file, trim silence and convert only <control>up to 15 seconds</control> of audio.
                                <emphasis>Limitation: max 300 models per request</emphasis>
                            </li>
                            <li><control>batch</control>: convert multiple files with a single model.
                                <emphasis>Limitation: max 100 files paths per request</emphasis>
                            </li>
                            <li><control>multi</control>: convert multiple files with multiple models
                                <emphasis>Limitation: max 20 files paths and 20 models per request</emphasis>
                            </li>
                        </list>
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>input.bypass_auto_pitch</td>
                    <td>required</td>
                    <td>boolean</td>
                    <td>Flag to bypass auto pitch correction for inference.
                        If set to true, only <code>f0up_key</code> will be used for conversion,
                        otherwise auto pitch correction will be detected and <code>f0up_key</code> will be adjusted by
                        that
                        value
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>input.f0method</td>
                    <td>required</td>
                    <td>string</td>
                    <td>The only valid value for now is <code>rmvpe</code></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>input.f0up_key</td>
                    <td>required</td>
                    <td>signed int</td>
                    <td>Valid range is from -18 to 18; representing pitch used for inference. Default value is 0</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>input.filepath</td>
                    <td>required</td>
                    <td>array</td>
                    <td>Array of strings. Each element is S3-compatible bucket path to the audio file
                        that needs to be processed. File must exist in the bucket. No starting slash.
                        Provide exactly one path for
                        <control>single</control> and <control>preview</control> processing modes and
                        multiple paths for <control>batch</control> and <control>multi</control> modes.
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>input.filter_radius</td>
                    <td>required</td>
                    <td>int</td>
                    <td>The valid range is from zero to 7.
                        If >=3: apply median filtering to the harvested pitch results.
                        The value represents the filter radius and can reduce breathing.
                        Default value is 3
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>input.index_rate</td>
                    <td>required</td>
                    <td>float</td>
                    <td>Allowed values from 0 to 1, used to set the model strength. Default value is 0</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>input.model_name</td>
                    <td>required</td>
                    <td>array</td>
                    <td>Array of strings. Each element is a valid name of a trained model that will be used for inference.
                        Model file must exist on S3. No .pth extension, only name.
                        Index file presence on S3 is optional. Provide exactly one model for
                        <control>single</control> and <control>batch</control> processing modes; at least one model
                        for <control>preview</control> mode and
                        multiple models for <control>multi</control> mode.

                        How to get the current list of models: <a href="Cloud-Database.topic">see this page</a>
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>input.protect</td>
                    <td>required</td>
                    <td>float</td>
                    <td>Valid values are from 0 to 0.5. Protect voiceless consonants and breath sounds to prevent
                        artifacts such as tearing in electronic music. Decrease the value to increase protection,
                        but it may reduce indexing accuracy. Set to 0.5 to disable. Default value is 0.3
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>input.resample_sr</td>
                    <td>required</td>
                    <td>int</td>
                    <td>If > 0, then resample the output audio in post-processing to the sample rate provided. Valid
                        values up
                        to 48000. Default value is zero for no resampling
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>input.rms_mix_rate</td>
                    <td>required</td>
                    <td>float</td>
                    <td>Adjust the volume envelope scaling. Closer to 0, the more it mimics the volume of the original
                        vocals.
                        Can help mask noise and make volume sound more natural when set relatively low.
                        Closer to 1 will be more of a consistently loud volume. Default value is 0.8
                    </td>
                </tr>
            </table>
        </chapter>
    </snippet>

